Hiptest template /demo / example Cucumber/Java

Tests are generated in Cucumber/Java format from Hiptest, using Hiptest publisher.

The examples are:

- show how tests are exported in Cucumber/Java.
- check exports work out of the box
- update tests
- integrate with Jenkins

To update the tests:

"hiptest-publisher -c cucumber-java-ci.conf --only=features,step_definitions"

Run tests

To build the project and run the tests, use the following command:

mvn clean test

The test report is generated in target/cuke-results-junit.xml